dork (plural dorks)

(US, derogatory slang) A quirky, silly and/or stupid person, or one who is out of touch with contemporary trends. Origin: late 1930's or early 1940's US.  A contraction for a "door key" child.  The term for a boy or girl who is (or was) left alone for long periods, locking themselves inside with little to do, while a single parent (or both parents) work.  Compare nerd, geek.
 
(vulgar slang) A whale's penis.